  <h3 class="no-margin subsection-header" data-anchor="sass-modules">
    Sass modules
    <small class="header-link">{{#link-to 'index' (query-params anchor='sass-modules')}}{{fa-icon 'link'}}{{/link-to}}</small>
  </h3>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">labs-ui/modules/[module]</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-5">
      <p>The consuming application's <code>app.scss</code> should first import Labs UI variables, then import Foundation, then include Foundation components, then import Labs UI modules before any custom app modules or styles.</p>
      <p>Labs UI has several Sass modules:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>labs-ui/modules/_base-typography</code></li>
        <li><code>labs-ui/modules/_m-color</code></li>
        <li><code>labs-ui/modules/_m-ember-tooltips</code></li>
        <li><code>labs-ui/modules/_m-layer-groups-menu</code></li>
        <li><code>labs-ui/modules/_m-site-header</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can either import these modules individually, or get them all by importing <code>labs-ui/all-modules</code>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-7">
      <p class="small-margin-bottom">This example <code>app.css</code> would get you everything:</p>
      <pre><code>@import 'labs-ui/variables';
@import 'foundation-sites/foundation'; // Foundation vars & mixins
@include foundation-everything; // Foundation components
@import 'labs-ui/all-modules';
</code></pre>
      <p class="small-margin-bottom">This one only gets you styles for specific components:</p>
      <pre><code>@import 'labs-ui/variables';

@import 'foundation-sites/foundation';

// Only include specific Foundation components
@include foundation-global-styles;
@include foundation-forms;
@include foundation-button;

// Only include specific Labs UI modules
@import 'modules/_base-typography';
@import 'modules/_m-color';
@import 'modules/_m-site-header';
</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>


