    <small class="header-link">{{#link-to 'index' (query-params anchor='background-color')}}{{fa-icon 'link'}}{{/link-to}}</small>
  </h3>
  <h4 class="dark-gray text-weight-normal">labs-ui/modules/_m-color</h4>
  <div class="grid-x grid-margin-x">
    <div class="cell large-6">
      <p>There is a <code>.bg-[color]</code> class for every Sass color variable. In addition to setting an element's background color, these classes also use Foundation's <code>color-pick-contrast()</code> Sass function to set the font color to either black or white for maximum contrast. </p>
      <p>Background color classes can be used in combination with font color classes. Since both classes have the same specificity, and <code>.[color]</code> rules follow <code>.bg-[color]</code> rules in the cascade order, font color classes will override the font color that's set by background color classes. </p>
      <pre><code>&lt;p class="bg-teal">.bg-teal&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="bg-teal-dark">.bg-teal-dark&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="bg-gold">.bg-gold&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="bg-gold gold-light">.bg-gold + .gold-light + &lt;span class="gold-dark">.gold-dark&lt;/span>&lt;/p></code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="cell large-6 text-center">
